               <head>Essay on suffering</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 " n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_972-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Essay interpreting the compensatory value of suffering through mystical principles, with multiple quotations from the works of known Ṣūfī authorities. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is not given a title, except from an endorsement on a later binding naming it as <title>Tasallīyat al-maṣāʾib</title>. The author similarly remains unidentified. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The volume is defective at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 22v): completed by <persName key="person_f7199" role="scr">Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad</persName> on 11 Muḥarram in regnal year 1 of <persName key="viaf_48143049" role="oth">Emperor Farrukh Siyar</persName> (=1125)/7 February 1713. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
